text: Loved this place. Always got my pizzas from here. Much better quality then anywhere else. Itâ€™s a shame itâ€™s closed for good. Very upsetting.

name: Kathy Morris
text: Great friendly service. Super menu, something for everyone!! They work fast and always explain how to cook the pizza. The offer salads,  cookie dough to make your own cookies, and other desserts that are yummy. The employees are great!@

name: Cordero Israel
text: A very tasty pizza sauce and for a good price too! Too bad they are closing up soon...

name: James Brady
text: Refound a family favorite. We moved away from our 1st Papa's.... found a new one near relatives we visit often. â€¦More

name: Shannon Walker
text: The pizzas are great but we love the customer service here. Nick went out of his way to make Mini Murph pizzas for my twin daughters because they had just sold the last few and my girls were disappointed.  He is always so friendly and provides great service. Thanks Nick!

name: Janell Vennard
text: My family has been going to papa Murphy's for many years and they have always had the same high quality ingredients for their pizzas. Gourmet and delicious! I have since moved to another state without papa Murphy's and can't wait to get a pizza from here every time I visit. I have never found a better pizza from anywhere else.

name: Nick S
text: Greatest take and bake Pizza you can find and their dissert pizza is fun.

name: N E
text: Drove 90 minutes to pick up a Papa Murphy's pizza for my son's birthday.  Being from the Northwest (where they're headquartered) we really miss them down here.  Hoping this location doesn't follow the others and shutdown.  Would add another hour to my drive to the next closest one.

name: NaDDDered V
text: Always the best freshest pizza you can get.

name: Emilee B
text: I'm so happy I found a Papa Murphy's near Me! I'm from the east coast and I'm in heaven! The employees were very friendly and the location was very clean!

name: Jane Shilling
text: Freshest, best tasting pizza in Eastvale,  Love that I can make it exactly how my family wants it and it only takes 12 minutes to bake!  Wow, now my kids will never have to eat cold delivery pizza again.  Also, try the Herb Chicken â€¦More

name: Pat Jones
text: Had a great experience. The was clean and good service . Had pizza for dinner, quite enjoyable. Will go again.

name: John Rizzardo
text: Excellent customer service and very good pizza!

name: christian
text: Out of regular crust pizza the day I came to their establishment. Drove a half hour out of my way, in gridlock, and 100 degree temps to grab pizza. In my opinion a business should be prepared for the day ahead with enough supplies not to â€¦More

name: Ray Tang
text: Love the deals they have. Staff is friendly and the place is always very clean. Great for quick stops on the way home to grab dinner.

name: Robert Reed
text: No longer in business, sad times and upset my son was his favorite pizza.

name: James W. Storey
text: Fantastic pizza. I loved the crust on the pie we had today. Highly recommend..

name: Nita M
text: Luv this place! Great prices and the thought of being able to bake a freshly made pizza to order is spectacular! It's a shame the Beaumont and Fontana locations were closed.

name: Ralph Perez
text: For a crispy crust you don't refrigerate after taking it home.  Best pizza deal.

name: philip quinn
text: Veteran owned, Good pizza, one of the only papa murph's left! Love the taco pizza circa cinco de mayo!

name: Janet Blackstock
text: Love Papa Murphy's Pizza lived in Washington that's what they have there and when I moved back to Inland Empire couldnt find one .now I see we have one at Eastvale I'm excited to go try them out love them I don't know why we don't have more Papa Murphy's pizza around

name: James Medina
text: Super fast and friendly. Pizza was bomb. Only problem I have is this is the only location near me and I live in redlands.

name: anne heffernan
text: The BEST PIZZA EVER!!!! I wish they had one in Corona. When I lived in Kansas we had one in Overland Park & it's hard to stay away from.  U deff get ur $$$ worth & their artichoke heart r huge...I love Papa Murphy's I just saw their commercial * about had a coronary.

name: Rachel Jackson
text: This restaurant has never let me down. The concept is quite clever. I would like to give special recognition to the fantastic workers Abby and Arianna! She was very helpful since I'm still not used to the menu! So thank you Abby, Arianna and Papa Murphy's. Keep doing what you're doing.

text: love their pizzas and I LOVE the take and bake option. Loaded with toppings and loads of cheese. It's our go to pizza place when we are in the area.
